# Shared Contracts — `packages/shared`

`packages/shared` is the **single source of truth** for all data contracts between `apps/web` and `apps/api`.

## Structure

```
packages/shared/src/
├── schemas/          # Zod schemas (one file per domain)
│   ├── booking.schema.ts
│   ├── order.schema.ts
│   ├── table.schema.ts
│   └── user.schema.ts
├── types/            # TypeScript types inferred from schemas
│   └── index.ts      # re-exports all z.infer<> types
├── constants/        # Enums, status codes, magic numbers
│   └── index.ts
└── query-keys.ts     # TanStack Query key factory
```

## Pattern: Schema-First

```typescript
// packages/shared/src/schemas/booking.schema.ts
import { z } from 'zod';

export const CreateBookingSchema = z.object({
  tableId: z.string().uuid(),
  slotId: z.string().uuid(),
  guestCount: z.number().int().min(1).max(20),
  specialRequests: z.string().max(500).optional(),
});

export type CreateBookingDto = z.infer<typeof CreateBookingSchema>;
```

```typescript
// apps/api — use schema for NestJS validation pipe
@UsePipes(new ZodValidationPipe(CreateBookingSchema))
@Post()
create(@Body() dto: CreateBookingDto) { ... }

// apps/web — use schema for React Hook Form resolver
const form = useForm<CreateBookingDto>({
  resolver: zodResolver(CreateBookingSchema),
});
```

## Rules
- ❌ NEVER duplicate type definitions in `apps/web` or `apps/api`
- ❌ NEVER import from `apps/*` inside `packages/shared`
- ✅ All API request/response bodies must have a corresponding Zod schema in `packages/shared`
- ✅ NestJS DTOs and RHF form types must be `z.infer<>` — never hand-written interfaces for API shapes
- ✅ Query key factories must live in `packages/shared/src/query-keys.ts`
